OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1773411079
OL,3,CFlying Scotsman locomotive returns to
OL,4,Cheritage steam railway
OL,6,FThe locomotive is 70 foot long and
OL,7,Fweighs 97 tonnes.
OL,9,FIn 1934, she was the first locomotive
OL,10,Fto officially reach 100mph in the UK,
OL,11,Fand also holds the world record for a
OL,12,Fnon-stop run in a steam locomotive,
OL,13,Fset in 1989 with a 422-mile trip.
OL,15,FThe railway icon was withdrawn from
OL,16,Fservice in 1963.
OL,18,FPrivate owners came and went and the
OL,19,Floco even travelled the globe to
OL,20,Fpromote Britain and trade, famously
OL,21,Fgoing to America from Liverpool docks.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1773411079
OL,3,CFlying Scotsman locomotive returns to
OL,4,Cheritage steam railway
OL,6,FThe National Railway Museum came to
OL,7,Fthe rescue and started a fund to buy
OL,8,Fand restore the Scotsman.
OL,10,FWork began in 2006 and a decade later
OL,11,Fshe returned to the tracks with
OL,12,Fthousands turning out to see her.
OL,14,FThe total cost of the restoration was
OL,15,F#4.2 million and the locomotive has
OL,16,Fsince travelled around the country,
OL,17,Fattracting countless rail enthusiasts.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
